import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['budgetYear'], data['value'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the trend of budget allocation over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['value'].hist(bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Value')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of forecast values?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.scatter(data['budgetYear'], data['value'], label='Budget')
    plt.scatter(data['forecastYear'], data['value'], label='Forecast')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the correlation between budget and forecast values?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('budgetYear')['value'].mean().reset_index()
    ax = plt.bar(data['budgetYear'], data['value'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average budget allocation per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
